    notes:
      "## Alpha-GPC vs CDP-Choline — Decision Frame\nBoth are bioavailable choline donors; the choice depends on use case priority:\n\n**Alpha-GPC advantages:**\n- Higher choline content per mg (~40% by weight vs CDP-Choline's ~18%)\n- Faster onset (~1 hour peak vs CDP-Choline's ~3 hours)\n- Stronger growth hormone effect (relevant for performance contexts)\n- More direct cholinergic effect — acute cognitive boost more subjectively perceptible\n- Better-evidence-supported for Alzheimer's adjunct (more European clinical trials)\n\n**CDP-Choline advantages:**\n- Provides cytidine → uridine release as secondary mechanism — uridine has independent neuroprotective and synthesis support effects\n- Better-evidence-supported in cognitive aging in healthy adults (less Alzheimer's-specific, more general aging)\n- Less hygroscopic, easier to formulate cleanly\n- Better tolerability profile at high doses\n- The cardiovascular safety signal that affects Alpha-GPC has not been associated with CDP-Choline\n\n**Practical recommendation:** for users wanting acute cognitive boost, growth hormone effect, or Alzheimer's adjunct → Alpha-GPC. For users wanting comprehensive cognitive-aging support with broader neuroprotective profile → CDP-Choline. Some users layer both — they have different secondary mechanisms (GH vs uridine) and are not strictly redundant.\n\n## Beginner Protocol\n300mg AM × 4 weeks. Track: cognitive function (memory, focus, mental clarity), mood, energy, sleep quality (Alpha-GPC's modest GH effect may improve sleep-phase recovery for some users). If positive subjective response, continue; if minimal effect, increase to 600mg or assess use case fit.\n\n## Advanced Protocol\n**Comprehensive cognitive stack:** Alpha-GPC 600mg/day + Lion's Mane 1000mg/day (NGF/BDNF complementary mechanism) + Huperzine A 100mcg cycled (substrate + breakdown inhibition) + Bacopa Monnieri 300mg/day (cholinergic + anti-inflammatory) + omega-3 high-DHA 2g/day + B-complex methylated (B12, folate) + creatine 5g/day. The Alpha-GPC + Huperzine A pairing specifically addresses cholinergic substrate AND breakdown — the mechanism rationale used in the Italian Alzheimer's clinical trials.\n\n**Pre-workout GH augmentation:** Alpha-GPC 600mg 60–90 minutes pre-workout. The GH spike is real and dose-dependent; effect size is meaningful for performance contexts. Combinations with caffeine + creatine + appropriate dietary fueling.\n\n**Pre-bed sleep-phase GH support:** Alpha-GPC 300mg pre-bed (1 hour before sleep) — supports the natural sleep-phase GH pulse. Less commonly used than pre-workout dosing but mechanistically rational.\n\n**Racetam stack substrate:** racetam-class compounds (aniracetam, phenylpiracetam, piracetam) increase cholinergic demand; choline donor pairing (Alpha-GPC or CDP-Choline) is standard practice. The 'racetam headache' is widely attributed to depleted choline pool — Alpha-GPC pairing prevents this in most users.\n\n## The Cardiovascular Signal — Honest Framing\nThe Lee 2021 Korean health insurance database study reported elevated stroke risk associated with chronic Alpha-GPC use over 10+ years. The finding has substantial methodological limitations:\n- **Observational, not RCT** — selection bias possible\n- **Confounding by indication** — Alpha-GPC is prescribed in Korea for cognitive disorders associated with cardiovascular disease; the underlying conditions may drive stroke risk rather than the supplement\n- **Single-database, single-country** — replication needed\n\nSubsequent analyses have produced mixed results. The signal hasn't been definitively confirmed but also hasn't been definitively refuted. For practical decisions:\n- **Low cardiovascular-risk users (younger, no risk factors):** the signal probably doesn't apply meaningfully; standard doses for typical use cases acceptable\n- **High cardiovascular-risk users (hypertension, atrial fibrillation, prior CV events, advanced atherosclerosis):** worth discussing with prescriber; CDP-Choline (no comparable signal) may be preferable\n- **Indefinite chronic high-dose use (>1200mg/day for years):** the most cautious approach is moderate dosing or cycling; the signal was associated with chronic high-dose use specifically\n\nThis is the kind of emerging signal where definitive guidance isn't possible and individual risk-benefit calculation matters.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\nN/A — oral capsule, tablet, or powder. Hygroscopic — keep sealed; consume powder forms quickly after opening. With or without food acceptable; modest food-effect on absorption. AM dosing for cognitive use; pre-workout (~60–90 min before) for GH augmentation; pre-bed for sleep-phase GH support.\n\n## Synergies\n**CDP-Choline:** complementary choline donor mechanism (different secondary effects: GH vs uridine). **Lion's Mane:** complementary cognitive mechanism (NGF/BDNF). **Huperzine A:** complementary cholinergic mechanism (substrate + breakdown inhibition — the standard cognitive-pharmacology pairing). **Aniracetam / Piracetam / Phenylpiracetam:** racetam class compounds increase cholinergic demand; choline donor pairing standard practice. **Bacopa Monnieri:** complementary cognitive mechanism. **Omega-3 high-DHA:** foundational neurosteroid + membrane support.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nDe Jesus Moreno 2003 (Italian, n=261 mild-moderate Alzheimer's, 1200mg/day × 180 days): improved cognitive function vs placebo on multiple measures. Parnetti 2007 (n=210 Alzheimer's adjunct to donepezil, 1200mg/day): improved cognitive outcomes vs donepezil alone. Bellar 2015 (n=13 healthy adults, 600mg single dose): improved isometric mid-thigh pull power. Ziegenfuss 2008 (n=7 active adults, 600mg pre-workout): improved peak bench press force. Lee 2021 (Korean health insurance database, observational): the cardiovascular signal discussed above.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nSubstantial Italian / European clinical evidence base for cognitive aging and Alzheimer's adjunct (the pharmaceutical regulatory pathway in those jurisdictions produced more clinical research than for most US-OTC supplements). Athletic / GH augmentation evidence emerging. Long real-world clinical use establishes general safety baseline; the cardiovascular signal warrants honest framing without overclaiming or dismissing.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: solid mechanistic case for choline donor + GH augmentation; substantial European clinical evidence in cognitive aging contexts; cardiovascular signal warrants honest framing. Anecdote: extensive use in nootropic and performance communities; subjective effects often perceptible (faster onset than many cognitive supplements); pairs naturally with racetam class. Decision frame: foundational cholinergic compound for comprehensive cognitive stacks; the GH augmentation feature is a relevant secondary benefit for performance contexts; the cardiovascular signal warrants prescriber discussion for higher-CV-risk users; CDP-Choline is the natural alternative for users where the CV signal is concerning.",
